article.headline: Marshall's 19 help Santa Clara knock off Duquesne 81-73
article.description: — Carlos Marshall Jr.'s 19 points helped Santa Clara defeat Duquesne 81-73 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Marshall's 19 help Santa Clara knock off Duquesne 81-73
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- — Carlos Marshall Jr.'s 19 points helped Santa Clara defeat Duquesne 81-73 on Saturday night. Marshall added six rebounds for the Broncos (9-5). Adama Bal shot 5 of 8 from the field and 8 for 11 from the foul line to add 19 points. Brenton Knapper had 12 points and finished 5 of 9 from the field. Dae Dae Grant led the way for the Dukes (8-3) with 32 points. Jimmy Clark III added 14 points for Duquesne. In addition, Kareem Rozier finished with six points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
